## Repository — bluefishforsale/homelab

### Structure

```
homelab/
├── playbooks/
│   ├── 00_site.yaml                    # Full infrastructure
│   ├── 01_base_system.yaml             # Base: packages, users, sysctl
│   ├── 02_core_infrastructure.yaml     # Core: Docker, DNS, DHCP
│   ├── 03_ocean_services.yaml          # Ocean: all application services
│   └── individual/
│       ├── base/                       # System-level playbooks
│       ├── core/                       # Network, storage, DNS/DHCP
│       ├── infrastructure/             # Docker, GPU, exporters, runners
│       └── ocean/                      # Per-service playbooks
│           ├── ai/                     #   llamacpp, open_webui, comfyui
│           ├── media/                  #   plex, sonarr, radarr, etc.
│           ├── monitoring/             #   prometheus, grafana
│           ├── network/                #   nginx, cloudflared, ddns
│           └── services/               #   nextcloud, tinacms, frigate
├── files/                              # Jinja2 templates per service
│   └── <service>/                      #   docker-compose.yml.j2, .service.j2, .env.j2
├── vars/
│   ├── vars_service_ports.yaml         # Centralized port assignments
│   ├── vars_cloudflared.yaml           # Tunnel ingress rules
│   └── vars_llamacpp_models.yaml       # LLM model definitions
├── vault/secrets.yaml                  # Encrypted secrets (ansible-vault)
├── inventories/production/hosts.ini    # Host inventory
└── Makefile                            # Validation targets
```

### Deployment Pattern

Every service follows: **playbook → templates → systemd → docker-compose**

```yaml
# Standard playbook structure
- name: Configure <service>
  hosts: ocean
  become: true
  vars_files:
    - ../../../../vault/secrets.yaml
    - ../../../../vars/vars_service_ports.yaml
  vars:
    service: <name>
    image: <docker-image>
    version: <tag>
    port: "{{ '{{' }} service_ports.<service>.port {{ '}}' }}"
    home: "/data01/services/{{ '{{' }} service {{ '}}' }}"
  tasks:
    - Create directories
    - Deploy docker-compose template  # notify: restart handler
    - Deploy systemd service template # notify: restart handler
    - Deploy .env template
    - Enable service
  handlers:
    - Reload systemd daemon
    - Restart <service> service
```

### Running Playbooks

```bash
# Single service deploy
ansible-playbook -i inventories/production/hosts.ini playbooks/individual/ocean/<category>/<service>.yaml

# Dry run
ansible-playbook -i inventories/production/hosts.ini playbooks/individual/ocean/<category>/<service>.yaml --check

# Syntax check
ansible-playbook -i inventories/production/hosts.ini playbooks/individual/ocean/<category>/<service>.yaml --syntax-check

# Full ocean services
ansible-playbook -i inventories/production/hosts.ini playbooks/03_ocean_services.yaml
```

### Validation

```bash
make validate           # All checks
make validate-yaml      # YAML syntax
make validate-ansible   # Ansible --syntax-check
make validate-templates # Jinja2 parsing
make security-scan      # Grep for hardcoded secrets
make check-vault        # Verify vault encrypted
```

