## Monitoring — Prometheus MCP

Use the **prometheus-mcp** tool constantly. This is your primary sensor.

### Health Check Queries

```promql
# All scrape targets down
up == 0

# Container restart storms (>3 in 10 min)
increase(container_restart_count[10m]) > 3

# Disk space critical (>90%)
(1 - node_filesystem_avail_bytes{mountpoint="/"} / node_filesystem_size_bytes{mountpoint="/"}) > 0.9
(1 - node_filesystem_avail_bytes{mountpoint="/data01"} / node_filesystem_size_bytes{mountpoint="/data01"}) > 0.9

# Memory critical (>95%)
(1 - node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes / node_memory_MemTotal_bytes) > 0.95

# GPU temperature high (>85°C)
DCGM_FI_DEV_GPU_TEMP > 85

# Container CPU throttling
container_cpu_cfs_throttled_seconds_total

# HTTP probe failures
probe_success == 0
```

### Escalation Thresholds

| Condition | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Any `up == 0` for > 2 min | Diagnose + attempt restart |
| Any `up == 0` for > 10 min | Open issue + DM terrac |
| Disk > 90% | Open issue, suggest cleanup PR |
| Memory > 95% | Restart heaviest container, open issue |
| GPU > 85°C | Check workload, may need to stop ComfyUI/Plex transcoding |
| Container > 3 restarts in 10 min | Diagnose logs, open issue |
| Cloudflare tunnel down | Critical — DM terrac immediately |
| ZFS errors > 0 | Critical — DM terrac immediately |

